<HEADLINE>
ADVERTISING NOTES
</HEADLINE>
 
(ATTN: Ore., Calif., New York, Minn.) (fb) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   SCHWAB CHOOSES BBDO NEW YORK
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Charles Schwab &AMP; Co. has awarded its consolidated
brand advertising account for financial services to BBDO New York,
part of the BBDO Worldwide unit of Omnicom Group. Billings were
estimated at $40 million to $50 million.
</P>
<P>
   ``BBDO's consistent track record with building brands like
General Electric and Visa convinced us they would be the right
partner,'' said Len Short, executive vice president for advertising
and brand management at Schwab in San Francisco. The assignments
being consolidated at BBDO New York had been handled by several
agencies, he added, like Lowe &AMP; Partners/SMS in San Francisco, part
of the Lowe Group unit of the Interpublic Group of Companies, and
Montgomery North in San Francisco, a spinoff of Kirshenbaum Bond &AMP;
Partners in New York that closed in December.
</P>
<P>
   The decision came after a brief review, Short said, that had
been narrowed to BBDO New York; Foote, Cone &AMP; Belding in San
Francisco, owned by True North Communications; the Venice, Calif.,
office of TBWA Chiat/Day, part of the TBWA Worldwide unit of
Omnicom, and Wieden &AMP; Kennedy in Portland, Ore.
</P>
<P>
   Suissa Miller Advertising in Los Angeles _ which was named last
month to handle Schwab's core brokerage account, including ads for
trading and online services _ will continue with those assignments.
</P>
<P>
   Another brokerage firm, Merrill Lynch &AMP; Co., may conclude a
review on its account, with billings estimated at more than $70
million, sometime this week.
</P>
<P>
   THREE ADS FOR NIKE WIN THE GRAND PRIX &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Three humorous commercials for Nike by Goodby,
Silverstein &AMP; Partners in San Francisco took top honors in the
competition for television and cinema work, winning the Grand Prix,
at the 45th annual International Advertising Festival in Cannes,
France.
</P>
<P>
   The spots, aimed at young skateboarders, present vignettes in
which athletes pursuing mainstream sports like golf, tennis, and
running are harassed and heckled _ treated, in other words, as
skateboarders often complain they are.
</P>
<P>
   Goodby, Silverstein, part of Omnicom Group, is one of two lead
agencies for Nike along with Wieden &AMP; Kennedy in Portland, Ore. The
timing of the honor was interesting because it came after
Advertising Age and Adweek published articles about the tug-of-war
between the two agencies for Nike's favor.
</P>
<P>
   Of the 23 gold awards, called Lions, presented on Saturday,
American agencies won 12. Fallon McElligott in Minneapolis won
three for three commercials for Miller Lite beer, sold by the
Miller Brewing Company unit of the Philip Morris Companies. The
Venice, Calif., office of TBWA Chiat/Day, part of the TBWA
Worldwide unit of Omnicom, won two: one for a commercial for the
Weather Channel, owned by Landmark Communications, and the other
for a commercial for the Play Station National Hockey League game
sold by Sony Computer Entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   Renzo Rosso, chairman of Diesel SpA, the Italian clothing
company whose tongue-in-cheek campaign won the Grand Prix in 1997
for television and cinema spots, accepted the award for advertiser
of the year.
</P>
<P>
   ACCOUNTS
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Seagate Technology Inc., Scotts Valley, Calif.,
expanded its relationship with its corporate brand agency, Foote,
Cone &AMP; Belding, San Francisco, part of True North Communications,
by awarding the agency additional duties for disk drive and tape
drive products. That account, with estimated billings of $12
million, had been handled by van Bronkhorst Group, Santa Clara,
Calif.
</P>
<P>
   Mastercard International Inc., Purchase, N.Y., to GSD&AMP;M, Austin,
Texas, a unit of Omnicom Group, to handle its Internet advertising,
which had been handled by Thunderhouse, a division of
McCann-Erickson World Group, New York, part of the Interpublic
Group of Companies. Billings were estimated at $5 million. GSD&AMP;M
already handles media services for Mastercard.
</P>
<P>
   MISCELLANY
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Kerr Kelly Thompson/Earle Palmer Brown, Greenwich,
Conn., a unit of Earle Palmer Brown, was renamed Earle Palmer
Brown.
</P>
</TEXT>
