<SLUG> BC-IRAN-ITALY-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ITALIAN LEADER TO VISIT IRAN THIS WEEK
</HEADLINE>
   (nk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEHRAN, Iran _ Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi will make an
official visit to Iran this week, the first by a head of government
from a European Union country since the 1979 revolution here,
Iranian and Italian officials say.
</P>
<P>
   Prodi, who is to arrive on Tuesday, is scheduled to meet
President Mohammed Khatami and former President Ali Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani. But there are no plans for Prodi to meet Iran's
spiritual leader, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Prodi has consulted with President Clinton and European leaders
and will report back to them upon his return, Ricardo Levi, Prodi's
spokesman, said in Rome on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The visit underscores a new willingness by the Europeans to
forge closer ties with Iran in the aftermath of Khatami's election
in May 1997. Khatami has tried to reach out to European and Arab
leaders, and he plans to address the U.N. General Assembly in New
York this fall. He and Clinton are scheduled to speak on the same
day, although in the absence of diplomatic relations, the two
presidents have no plans to meet. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
