<HEADLINE>
CELEBRATE YOUR INDEPENDENCE FROM THE NBA
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ It's a clash between the stinking rich and the
comfortably wealthy, where the placement of the decimal points
means more than the points-per-game averages, and Michael Jordan's
impact on the future of the collective bargaining agreement will
have everyone holding their collective breaths.
</P>
<P>
   Sometime after the NBA lockout rears its Stern-like head
Wednesday, there will be a point when the players making minimum
wage will question a system that rewards a tiny few at the expense
of a bunch of others.
</P>
<P>
   And it is there they'll be hit with a taste of what it's like in
the real world.
</P>
<P>
   _The irony is that Larry Bird will be honored today as the
newest member of basketball's Hall of Fame, two days before the NBA
shuts down, in part, because of haggling over the so-called ``Larry
Bird exception.''...
</P>
<P>
   _BING-Olowokandi!...
</P>
<P>
   _In the NBA, ``potential'' remains the hottest buzzword a player
can have pinned on him. It's not illustrated just in Michael
Olowokandi's situation. Imagine how two second-round picks in '98,
UCLA's Toby Bailey and Arizona's Miles Simon, would have done if
they'd come out for the draft after their team's NCAA title
season....
</P>
<P>
   _It's tough trusting anything Jerry West says when he prefaces
everything with: ``To be candid with you...''...
</P>
<P>
   _ This week's edition of ``The Writing's On (And Off) The Wall''
is presented by...
</P>
<P>
   (begin ital)Let's see here...
</P>
<P>
   We must have sold out to someone by now...
</P>
<P>
   Ah, here it is...(end ital)
</P>
<P>
   ABSOLUTELY NOBODY.
</P>
<P>
   Meaning: NO BANK, NO AIRLINE, NO OFFICE SUPPLY DISCOUNT STORE,
NO OUTLET MALL, NO FLOPPY DISC MASS PRODUCER, NO QUALCOMM (whatever
that is), NO DEPARTMENT STORE, AND DEFINITELY NO PHONE COMPANY.
</P>
<P>
   And for the record, we just switched our long-distance service
to carrier pigeons....
</P>
<P>
   _It's only a matter of time before the drips at DWP decide they
can't live another day without being Dodger Stadium's new title
sponsor, following the lead of Edison Field in Anaheim....
</P>
<P>
   _Finally, the Dodgers rid themselves of that cancer Mark Cresse
after 24 seasons and started focusing on winning a pennant....
</P>
<P>
   _The Dodger Stadium fans haven't been booing, they're just
saying ``RUUUUUUUUUUUPERT''....
</P>
<P>
   _Why doesn't Tommy Lasorda just marry Bobby Valentine and get it
over with?...
</P>
<P>
   _Short list of the Dodgers managerial candidates for '99: 1.
Kevin Kennedy, 2. Davey Lopes, a distant 3. Jim Leyland...
</P>
<P>
   _The Clippers should have such a list of glowing candidates to
choose from....
</P>
<P>
   _The writers who hint that Lasorda will be the one to re-sign
Mike Piazza in the offseason are the same ones who continue to
perpetuate the myth that Uncle Tommy is Piazza's godfather....
</P>
<P>
   _Orel Hershiser just misses pitching against the Dodgers in this
Fourth of July weekend series, but he'll catch the final game of
the Angels series instead....
</P>
<P>
   _If Hideo Nomo stays every fifth day in the Mets' rotation,
he'll make an appearance during the Saturday stops of both
four-game series that the Mets have with the Dodgers in New York
(July 31-Aug. 3) and in L.A. (Aug. 28-31)....
</P>
<P>
   _Eric Karros said the most surreal thing he's seen lately was on
TV last week when Nomo was pitching to Piazza with Todd Zeile at
the plate....
</P>
<P>
   _Given a choice between the Dodgers' ``Think Blue'' pullovers or
the hideous Giants pullovers from the Ed Halicki era in the '70s,
we'd take neither....
</P>
<P>
   _If Adrian Beltre was a call-up just to showcase to the Seattle
brass in a possible Randy Johnson deal _ and no matter what the
Mariners say, they're still going to get rid of him _ the Dodgers
might now be forced to keep him....
</P>
<P>
   _At a ``symposium'' that the NFL makes all its rookie draft
picks go through this week, Denver quarterback John Elway and some
retired players will lead a discussion on ``Success in the NFL and
Life After Football.''...
</P>
<P>
   _So the American soccer team leaves France kicking and
screaming. Which, if it did that on the field, might have meant an
extended visit.... &QL;
</P>
