<HEADER>
A0864 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      06-28 0261
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Monday, June 29 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   FILMS-FOURTH (Los Angeles) With ``Armageddon,'' Disney has
staked out the Fourth of July weekend, Hollywood's traditional
launching pad for summer blockbusters, with the tried-and-true
recipe of slam-bang action. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   TEEN-DRIVING (Los Angeles) California teen-agers are scrambling
to get their driver licenses before Wednesday, when new
restrictions take effect that will alter the dynamics of the
state's storied car culture. By Melissa Schmitt. (Will move in the
``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BOX-OFFICE (Los Angeles) Eddie Murphy continued forays into
family fare have paid off, as the star's ``Dr. Dolittle'' took in
an estimated $29 million over its opening weekend, while ``Mulan,''
featuring Murphy's voice, took second place with $16.7 million. By
Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national
news files.)
</P>
<P>
   GAY-PRIDE (Los Angeles) The 28th annual Gay and Lesbian Pride
Festival drew hundreds of thousands of people to West Hollywood for
events including a parade and a 5- or 10K run led by Olympic
champion Greg Louganis. By Leilani Albano.
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news
files.)
</P>
