   (NYT12) NEW YORK -- June 28, 1998 -- NY-RUSSIAN-ENTREPRENEUR,
6-28 -- In less than six years, Russian entreprenuer Felix Komarov
has become a patron of culture and charitable causes, founded a
weekly Russian-language newspaper in New York and started a
Rolls-Royce dealership in Moscow. And just this month, he opened a
lavish three-story Russian cabaret-restaurant on the East Side of
Manhattan. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) OAKLAND, Calif -- June 28, 1998 -- AT&AMP;T-TCI, 6-28 --
Charles Vandagriff talks to his daughter Rachel, as his wife, Kathy
Sinsheimer, watches their other daughter, Corinne, at a computer.
Their Oakland household is one of millions with multiple PC's and
phone lines. Someday, AT&AMP;T wants families like the Vandagriffs to
turn to the company for one-stop shopping for not only all of their
telephone and cable television services but new information
services as well. (Dan Krauss/New York Times Photo)
</P>
